729a294d-f287-4492-8bb7-18230fda9b8b	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	âš–ï¸ Legal Research Request	\N	f	1761699226	1761699249	{"id": "", "title": "\\u2696\\ufe0f Legal Research Request", "models": ["deepseek-v3.1:671b"], "params": {}, "history": {"messages": {"6df32def-b611-44b7-9de1-fe1e06eb76fb": {"id": "6df32def-b611-44b7-9de1-fe1e06eb76fb", "parentId": null, "childrenIds": ["00e82e87-7032-44f2-8138-0a594936f54d"], "role": "user", "content": "You are a senior legal research assistant. Today is 2025-10-29.\\nResearch the legal issue below and return the answer in a clean, practitioner-ready brief.\\n  \\nMatter Type: Criminal\\nJurisdiction: Kenya\\nDate Range Start:\\nDate Range End:\\nPrimary Sources Focus: Statutes & Regulations\\nCitation Style: Kenya Law (eKLR-style)\\nDepth: Practitioner Level\\n  \\nIssue/Question (what must be answered):\\nTest\\n  \\nRelevant Facts (bullet points):\\n  \\n  \\nKnown Authorities (optional list):\\n  \\n  \\nOutput exactly this structure:\\n1) Short Answer (2\\u20134 sentences, include standard of review if apt)\\n2) Governing Rule(s) (with precise citations)\\n3) Analysis (apply rule to facts; include split authority if any; note open questions)\\n4) Key Precedents Table (Case | Court/Year | Holding | How it helps/hurts | Citation)\\n5) Statutes/Regs (Section-by-section relevance; amendments within date range)\\n6) Distinguishing Factors & Counterarguments\\n7) Practical Guidance / Risk Notes\\n8) Bibliography (primary then secondary). If a citation cannot be verified, tag it as [Not verified].\\n  \\nDo not invent citations. Prefer authoritative reporters or official law websites. Where authority is thin in chosen jurisdiction, suggest most persuasive analogies (and label them clearly).", "timestamp": 1761699225, "models": ["deepseek-v3.1:671b"]}, "00e82e87-7032-44f2-8138-0a594936f54d": {"parentId": "6df32def-b611-44b7-9de1-fe1e06eb76fb", "id": "00e82e87-7032-44f2-8138-0a594936f54d", "childrenIds": [], "role": "assistant", "content": "", "model": "glm-4.6", "modelName": "glm-4.6", "modelIdx": 0, "timestamp": 1761699225, "error": {"content": "400: Model 'glm-4.6:latest' was not found"}, "done": true}, "d16133e1-39c7-4359-8ebd-5bac8a0dd23c": {"id": "d16133e1-39c7-4359-8ebd-5bac8a0dd23c", "parentId": null, "childrenIds": ["7d1acb85-b311-4dd9-b101-dab7496e9392"], "role": "user", "content": "You are a senior legal research assistant. Today is 2025-10-29.\\nResearch the legal issue below and return the answer in a clean, practitioner-ready brief.\\n  \\nMatter Type: Criminal\\nJurisdiction: Kenya\\nDate Range Start:\\nDate Range End:\\nPrimary Sources Focus: Statutes & Regulations\\nCitation Style: Kenya Law (eKLR-style)\\nDepth: Practitioner Level\\n  \\nIssue/Question (what must be answered):\\nTest\\n  \\nRelevant Facts (bullet points):\\n  \\n  \\nKnown Authorities (optional list):\\n  \\n  \\nOutput exactly this structure:\\n1) Short Answer (2\\u20134 sentences, include standard of review if apt)\\n2) Governing Rule(s) (with precise citations)\\n3) Analysis (apply rule to facts; include split authority if any; note open questions)\\n4) Key Precedents Table (Case | Court/Year | Holding | How it helps/hurts | Citation)\\n5) Statutes/Regs (Section-by-section relevance; amendments within date range)\\n6) Distinguishing Factors & Counterarguments\\n7) Practical Guidance / Risk Notes\\n8) Bibliography (primary then secondary). If a citation cannot be verified, tag it as [Not verified].\\n  \\nDo not invent citations. Prefer authoritative reporters or official law websites. Where authority is thin in chosen jurisdiction, suggest most persuasive analogies (and label them clearly).", "models": ["deepseek-v3.1:671b"], "timestamp": 1761699235}, "7d1acb85-b311-4dd9-b101-dab7496e9392": {"parentId": "d16133e1-39c7-4359-8ebd-5bac8a0dd23c", "id": "7d1acb85-b311-4dd9-b101-dab7496e9392", "childrenIds": [], "role": "assistant", "content": "**1) Short Answer**\\nThe provided query is insufficient to provide a legal brief. The issue/question is stated only as \\"Test,\\" and no relevant facts have been supplied. A practitioner-ready brief requires a specific legal question and a set of material facts to which the law can be applied. Without these elements, any analysis would be purely speculative and not actionable.\\n\\n**2) Governing Rule(s)**\\n*   **Civil Procedure Rules, 2010**, Order 3 Rule 2(1)(c): Requires a plaint to contain a brief summary of the material facts on which the party relies. This principle of requiring material facts for a coherent claim is analogous to the need for specific facts to conduct legal research.\\n*   **General Practice:** Effective legal analysis is contingent upon a clearly defined legal issue and a concrete set of facts to which the law is applied.\\n\\n**3) Analysis**\\nThe request does not meet the minimum threshold for legal research. The term \\"Test\\" is ambiguous and could refer to a standard of proof, a legal test from a specific area of law (e.g., the test for insanity under the Penal Code, the test for bail, or the test for constitutional validity), or a procedural test. In the absence of a defined issue and facts, it is impossible to identify the relevant governing rules, conduct an analysis, or compile a list of authorities. The output structure requested (e.g., Key Precedents Table, Statutes/Regs) cannot be populated meaningfully.\\n\\n**4) Key Precedents Table**\\n*Not applicable due to the lack of a defined legal issue.*\\n\\n**5) Statutes/Regs**\\n*Not applicable due to the lack of a defined legal issue.*\\n\\n**6) Distinguishing Factors & Counterarguments**\\nThe primary counterargument is that the researcher should infer a common legal issue. However, this is poor practice as it risks answering the wrong question entirely. The responsibility lies with the instructing party to provide clear and specific instructions.\\n\\n**7) Practical Guidance / Risk Notes**\\n*   **Guidance:** To receive a useful brief, re-submit the query with:\\n    1.  A precise legal question (e.g., \\"What is the legal test for establishing the defence of provocation under Kenyan law?\\").\\n    2.  A bulleted list of the key, material facts of the case.\\n    3.  Any specific known authorities or jurisdictions of interest.\\n*   **Risk:** Proceeding with legal research or advice based on an undefined \\"Test\\" and no facts carries a high risk of generating irrelevant, inaccurate, or misleading information, which could have serious adverse consequences for a client's matter.\\n\\n**8) Bibliography**\\n*   **Primary Sources:** *Civil Procedure Rules, 2010* (Kenya).\\n*   **Secondary Sources:** None applicable.", "model": "deepseek-v3.1:671b", "modelName": "deepseek-v3.1:671b", "modelIdx": 0, "timestamp": 1761699235, "lastSentence": "8) Bibliography\\n   Primary Sources: Civil Procedure Rules, 2010* (Kenya).", "usage": {"response_token/s": "N/A", "prompt_token/s": "N/A", "total_duration": 9064287387, "load_duration": 0, "prompt_eval_count": 277, "prompt_tokens": 277, "prompt_eval_duration": 0, "eval_count": 573, "completion_tokens": 573, "eval_duration": 0, "approximate_total": "0h0m9s", "total_tokens": 850, "completion_tokens_details": {"reasoning_tokens": 0, "accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}}, "done": true, "followUps": ["Can you give me examples of common legal tests used in Kenyan criminal law?", "What specific information should I include in the 'Relevant Facts' section for a criminal law brief?", "How do I formulate a proper legal question for a criminal matter in Kenya?", "What are the most authoritative sources for Kenyan criminal statutes and case law?"]}}, "currentId": "7d1acb85-b311-4dd9-b101-dab7496e9392"}, "messages": [{"id": "d16133e1-39c7-4359-8ebd-5bac8a0dd23c", "parentId": null, "childrenIds": ["7d1acb85-b311-4dd9-b101-dab7496e9392"], "role": "user", "content": "You are a senior legal research assistant. Today is 2025-10-29.\\nResearch the legal 