COPY public.prompt (id, command, user_id, title, content, "timestamp", access_control) FROM stdin;
1	/legal-research	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	Legal Research	You are a senior legal research assistant. Today is {{CURRENT_DATE}}.\nResearch the legal issue below and return the answer in a clean, practitioner-ready brief.\n\nMatter Type: {{matter_type | select:options=["Civil","Criminal","Commercial","Constitutional","Administrative","Employment","Family","IP","Tax","Banking/Finance","Procurement","Environmental","Competition"]}}\nJurisdiction: {{jurisdiction | select:options=["Kenya","EAC (East Africa)","Uganda","Tanzania","Rwanda","South Africa","United Kingdom","United States (Federal)","India","EU"]}}\nDate Range Start: {{date_start | date}}\nDate Range End: {{date_end | date}}\nPrimary Sources Focus: {{primary_focus | select:options=["Case Law","Statutes & Regulations","Mixed/Best Available"]:default="Mixed/Best Available"}}\nCitation Style: {{citation_style | select:options=["OSCOLA","Bluebook","Kenya Law (eKLR-style)","APA (for secondary)"]:default="OSCOLA"}}\nDepth: {{depth | select:options=["Quick Overview","Practitioner Level","Exhaustive"]:default="Practitioner Level"}}\n\nIssue/Question (what must be answered): \n{{issue | textarea:placeholder="State the specific legal question(s)":required}}\n\nRelevant Facts (bullet points): \n{{facts | textarea:placeholder="Salient, dispute-relevant facts only"}}\n\nKnown Authorities (optional list): \n{{known_authorities | textarea:placeholder="e.g., case names, statutes, sections"}}\n\nOutput exactly this structure:\n1) Short Answer (2â€“4 sentences, include standard of review if apt)\n2) Governing Rule(s) (with precise citations)\n3) Analysis (apply rule to facts; include split authority if any; note open questions)\n4) Key Precedents Table (Case | Court/Year | Holding | How it helps/hurts | Citation)\n5) Statutes/Regs (Section-by-section relevance; amendments within date range)\n6) Distinguishing Factors & Counterarguments\n7) Practical Guidance / Risk Notes\n8) Bibliography (primary then secondary). If a citation cannot be verified, tag it as [Not verified].\n\nDo not invent citations. Prefer authoritative reporters or official law websites. Where authority is thin in chosen jurisdiction, suggest most persuasive analogies (and label them clearly).\n	1761698718	{}
2	/case-brief--ratioobiter-extractor	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	Case Brief / Ratioâ€“Obiter Extractor	Create a precise case brief from the provided judgment text (or clipboard if text is left blank).\n\nJurisdiction: {{jurisdiction | select:options=["Kenya","Uganda","Tanzania","Rwanda","South Africa","UK","US (Federal)","India","EU"]}}\nInclude Parallel Citations? {{include_parallel | checkbox}}\nInclude Paragraph Pins? {{include_para_pins | checkbox:default=true}}\nDepth: {{depth | select:options=["Student Summary","Practitioner Brief","Headnote-Style Digest"]:default="Practitioner Brief"}}\n\nJudgment Text (paste; leave blank to use clipboard):\n{{judgment_text | textarea:placeholder="Paste full judgment text here"}}\n\nIf {{judgment_text}} is blank, use {{CLIPBOARD}}.\n\nReturn:\n- Caption, Court, Judge(s), Date\n- Procedural Posture\n- Issues (enumerated)\n- Holding(s) (yes/no answers to each issue)\n- Rule(s) / Test(s)\n- Ratio decidendi vs. Obiter dicta (clearly separated)\n- Material Facts\n- Reasoning (with paragraph pins if available)\n- Disposition\n- Key Quotes (â‰¤ 5)\n- Citations list (validated; mark [Not verified] if unsure)\n	1761698780	{}
3	/iraccreac-argument-builder-side-specific	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	IRAC/CREAC Argument Builder (Side-Specific)	Build a persuasive written submission using the {{structure | select:options=["IRAC","CREAC","CRuPAC"]:default="CREAC"}} format for the selected side.\n\nSide: {{side | select:options=["Appellant","Respondent","Prosecution","Defence","Applicant","Respondent (Judicial Review)"]}}\nJurisdiction: {{jurisdiction | select:options=["Kenya","EAC","UK","US (Federal)","India","South Africa"]}}\nCitation Style: {{citation_style | select:options=["OSCOLA","Bluebook","Kenya Law (eKLR-style)"]:default="OSCOLA"}}\nTarget Length (words): {{target_words | number:default=900}}\nTone: {{tone | select:options=["Neutral-judicial","Firm-advocacy","Concise-technical","Plain-English"]:default="Firm-advocacy"}}\n\nQuestion Presented:\n{{question | textarea:required}}\n\nMaterial Facts (bullet points):\n{{facts | textarea:required}}\n\nAuthorities You Must Use (optional):\n{{mandatory_auth | textarea}}\n\nDeliver:\n- Heading structure for {{structure}}\n- Arguments with numbered points\n- Counterarguments & rebuttals\n- Relief sought\n- Short conclusion\n	1761698823	{}
4	/citation-normalizer--checker	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	Citation Normalizer & Checker	Normalize and validate legal citations. Identify broken, incomplete, or non-standard cites and propose corrected versions.\n\nCitation Style: {{style | select:options=["OSCOLA","Bluebook","Kenya Law (eKLR-style)","APA (secondary)"]:default="OSCOLA"}}\nStrictness: {{strictness | select:options=["Lenient (tolerate abbreviations)","Standard","Strict (enforce full style)"]:default="Standard"}}\n\nPaste citations (one per line):\n{{citations | textarea:required}}\n\nReturn a table:\nOriginal | Normalized | Style Notes | Reporter/Neutral Cite | Status [Valid/Not verified] | URL (official if possible)\n	1761698873	{}
5	/precedent-comparator-case-vs-case	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	Precedent Comparator (Case vs Case)	Compare two authorities for similarity, strength, and applicability to the stated issue.\n\nFocus: {{focus | select:options=["Facts","Issues","Holdings","Reasoning","Outcome","All"]:default="All"}}\nWeight Recency? {{weight_recency | checkbox}}\nJurisdiction Priority: {{juris_priority | select:options=["Same jurisdiction first","Persuasive foreign allowed","Any credible source"]:default="Same jurisdiction first"}}\n\nIssue:\n{{issue | textarea:required}}\n\nCase A (paste excerpt or summary + citation):\n{{case_a | textarea:required}}\n\nCase B (paste excerpt or summary + citation):\n{{case_b | textarea:required}}\n\nOutput:\n- Side-by-side matrix (Facts/Issues/Holding/Reasoning/Outcome)\n- Points of alignment and distinction\n- Which case is stronger and why\n- How to distinguish the weaker case\n- Practical usage notes (when to cite which)\n	1761698892	{}
6	/statute--regulation-analyzer	9b013030-56f5-4c63-ba8e-5761787d0787	Statute / Regulation Analyzer	Analyze the statute/regulation text and produce a practitioner map.\n\nJurisdiction: {{jurisdiction | select:options=["Kenya","EAC","UK","US (Federal)","EU","India","South Africa"]}}\nSections of Interest (comma-separated): {{sections | text:placeholder="e.g., 2, 5(3), 12A"}}\nTrack Amendments? {{track_amend | checkbox:default=true}}\n\nStatute / Regulation Text:\n{{statute_text | textarea:required}}\n\nDeliver:\n- Definitions & scope\n- Elements/requirements checklists per section\n- Cross-references and implied powers\n- Amendments timeline (if text shows them)\n- Common pitfalls / compliance traps\n- Open interpretive questions\n	1761698928	{}
